veloping these ideas. As well as providing space for some &#8216;blue sky thinking&#8217; about aspirational projects in the future.<br \/>\n<!--more--><\/p>\n<p>Representing EdLab experiences. This links in with our ongoing aim to apply the university&#8217;s E3 agenda through utilising Grace&#8217;s research into student employability. In this part of the session, Grace introduced students to the STAR approach for articulating skills:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Situation<\/li>\n<li>Task<\/li>\n<li>Action<\/li>\n<li>Result<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>We then helped them to build a LinkedIn profile in order to represent these skills and experiences more widely, as well as facilitating them to build a professional network. Student Nicola Roberts said this was a &#8216;revelation&#8217; to her, and students have since been working ont heir profiles and &#8216;Linking In&#8217; with contacts.<\/p>\n<p>SIGN UP TO OUR NEXT SESSION 03.02.16:<\/p>\n<p>https:\/\/<a href=\"https:\/\/the3rsedlabsession.eventbrite.co.uk\">the3rsedlabsession.eventbrite.co.uk<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>References<\/p>\n<p>Kim, J.T. &amp; Lee, W. (2015), &#8220;Dynamical model for gamification of learning (DMGL)&#8221;, <i>Multimedia Tools and Applications, <\/i>vol. 74, no. 19, pp. 8483-8493.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Our 3 Rs session is designed to give EdLab students the chance to reflect, redesign and represent their EdLab experience. Reflection was facilitated by discussing EdLab projects with the group. Within this session we had students who had worked on an education pack for a local theatre company, a science and poetry session for year [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":66,"featured_media":758,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[44],"tags":[105,106],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v15.6.2 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<met